name: 2010 Elky Shiraz
description:
Built to last although already very approachable. Hints of chocolate and blackberry. 
Very smooth, a supurb example of the fruit of this region, handmade with attention to detail.
This wine has been entered in one competition, the Hong Kong International Wine & Spirit Competion 2012. Results were a trophy and a gold medal in the 'Best Wines With Asian Dishes" category, and a bronze medal in the "Best Red Wine" category.
$200 per case (dozen bottles)- Delivered in Australia

name: 2010 Cleanskin
description:
Silky smooth Shiraz, the fruit is able to speak for itself. Delicious.
Can be enjoyed now, or if cellared correctly until 2020.
$110 per case (dozen bottles)- Delivered in Australia
